subject: Boxing
lead_paragraph: The United States flyweight Rau’shee Warren took another step toward returning to the Olympics yesterday by easily defeating the 2004 Olympian Tulashboy Doniyorov of Uzbekistan in a 20-8 decision at the World Boxing Championships in Chicago.Warren needs to win his next two fights to qualify for Beijing. He is attempting to become the first American boxer in more than 20 years to compete in two Olympics.Warren never trailed Doniyorov and took control in the second round, knocking him down.
